commit.message:
Fixed quitting conditions

Added logic that prevents game over with 0 points

More screen size adjustments

Specifically fullscreen capabilities

Updated gameover condition

The game now ends when the user presses the button once more

Changed input of "bumper" to 2

i.e. we will receive an integer rather than a string to denote point earnings

Merge pull request #4 from maryamkaka/bumper

Changed bumper registration value to 2

Merge pull request #3 from maryamkaka/bumpers

Added Start button recognition

Merge pull request #2 from maryamkaka/bumpers

Bumpers
Fixed Arduino COM port to match serial port on the Raspberry Pi

Addition of scoring screen

After having inserted the quarter, it is time to actually play the game, so implemented right now is a scoring screen that is currently dependent on the passage of time. Game over is also present and also displays the score the user has achieved.

Implemented Reset Game 

Pressing "r" resets the game (i.e. go back to the initial "not-paid" state). Pressing "r" can be changed to any more appropriate event
Clicking moves on to the next screen (TODO: actual game screen), though clicking will be changed soon to take into account pinball machine usage (either on a time basis or whenever the player hits a button on the actual pinball machine)

Changed word placements

The blinking "insert coins" at the bottom of the screen did not appear until a coin was inserted. This was remedied by changing it to a variant of "thanks for paying"; since it displays after inserting a quarter, and I haven't found a way to change it before or after. 
With this update, the "please pay up" statement is now unblinking and is placed directly under the title screen, and does not disappear after payment.
Modified CoinReader to Output voolan trigger for correct coin
